messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /printshops

All HTTP methods acceptable:
- false

Method support (based on the source code only):
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- In PrintShopController there is a method annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops", method = RequestMethod.GET) which explicitly maps GET requests to the path "/printshops" (see the getPrintShops() method). No other @RequestMapping for the exact path "/printshops" is present in the provided source.
- Because only a GET mapping is declared in the code for that path, only GET is considered acceptable when determining support "based on the code, not on experiential assumptions." The controller class has no class-level @RequestMapping prefix that would modify the path.
- There are no explicit mappings for HEAD, POST, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE or PATCH for "/printshops" in the provided source, so those are marked not acceptable per the instruction to rely on the code only. (Note: frameworks sometimes implicitly handle HEAD/OPTIONS for GET mappings at runtime, but that behavior is not used here because the task requires using only the explicit code mappings.)
